snippet.textDisplay: I can also tell you were using a E6010 rod. Those rods when you first use them stick like hell. The first rod you want to use is the E6013, welders call it a dummy rod because it’s easy to strike and maintain the arc. It’s only used for flat position welding. Other rods like E7018 are used for all positions.

snippet.textDisplay: THE BEST WAY for you to learn how to weld, MIG or Stick is to weld a bead pad. It’s just a flat plate( 4”x4”) and stacking beads next to each other. Then once you get that down you can play with the settings and do uphill, downhill, and over head. I just graduated HS and I built a trailer for my grandpa, with only a few months of MIG experience. All you gotta do is get yourself a nice workspace, lots of metal, and lots of rods and mig wire to burn. You’ll get it done if you put ur mind to it. I love ya, and I’ll see ya next time!
snippet.textOriginal: THE BEST WAY for you to learn how to weld, MIG or Stick is to weld a bead pad. It’s just a flat plate( 4”x4”) and stacking beads next to each other.
